requently Asked Questions Bachelor of Science  B S  Programs The Computer Science Department offers the Bachelor of Science  B S  program in Computer Science  along with an optional Programs or Programs concentration  Bachelor of Science  B S  program Programs concentration Admission to the undergraduate Computer Science programs is administered by the UIC College of Engineering and the UIC Office of Admissions and Records  UIC College of Engineering UIC Office of Admissions and Records Special Programs The Guaranteed Professional Program Admissions initiative  GPPA  each Fall admits up to     highly qualified entering freshmen with admission guaranteed  if undergraduate course and performance criteria are met  to one of more than    professional degree programs Guaranteed Professional Program Admissions initiative  GPPA  In addition  the College of Engineering offers special financial aid opportunities to highly qualified applicants to the GPPA program College of Engineering offers special financial aid opportunities After they have been admitted to UIC  all incoming freshmen with an ACT composite score of at least    or an SAT total score of       and who rank in the top    percent of their high school class  are invited to join the Honors College  membership is not automatic  students must submit an application Honors College Honors College students enjoy access to honors classes and seminars  an Honors College Fellow  undergraduate research opportunities  special scholarships  extended library privileges  and Access to Honors College facilities  computer lab  lounge  quiet study room  etc Apply for admission to the program The UIC Office of Admissions and Records  OAR  is responsible for evaluating all undergraduate student applications  and your first step is to complete the UIC Undergradutate Application  Select "Engineering" as your choice of programs  You may complete the application in one of three ways  UIC Office of Admissions and Records  OAR Apply  Undergraduate Open House Each year we have several undergraduate Open House events  This will help you get a feel for the faculty  students  and research in our department  You can register online and get additional information on the dates and times Open House events   Financial Aid The UIC Office of Student Financial Aid provides information on scholarships  fellowships  loans  and student work study opportunities for both incoming and continuing students  The College of Engineering also offers special scholarships restricted to Engineering students Office of Student Financial Aid special scholarships restricted to Engineering students Scholarships The Department of Computer Science offers scholarships to outstanding first year students  If you are interested in applying for a Computer Science scholarship  please contact recruit cs uic edu for more information recruit cs uic edu  The CS Scholars program offers         per year scholarships targeted towards financially needy undergraduate women  Latino  African American and Native Americans  This is for both entering Freshman as well as Transfer students CS Scholars  The SFS  Scholarships for Service  program offers a stipend of         year and Tuitions and Fees waivers  The program supports junior and senior students interested in cybersecurity and electronic security courses Housing UIC offers on campus housing for undergraduate and graduate students  Housing information and applications are available through the UIC UIC Student Organizations Undergraduate students have the opportunity to participate in a broad array of student organizations  The Student organizations resource home page describes campus wide organizations  In addition  the College of Engineering sponsors a wide range of student activities and organizations College of Engineering  Of special interest to Computer Science students  UIC sponsors local chapters of the Association for Computing Machinery and the Institute of Electrical and Electronic Engi